1
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:03,016
She looks at me every day.

2
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,977
Mary Jane Watson.

3
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:09,189
Oh, boy. If she only knew
how I felt about her.

4
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:11,149
But she can never know.

5
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:14,778
I made a choice once to live
a life of responsibility.

6
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:17,239
A life she can never be a part of.

7
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:18,699
Who am I?

8
00:03:18,866 --> 00:03:21,451
I'm Spider-Man, given a job to do.

9
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:24,621
And I'm Peter Parker,
and I, too, have a job.

10
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:26,373
Parker. Parker!

11
00:03:26,832 --> 00:03:28,792
No, no, no, stop! Stop!

12
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,880
Parker, you're late, man. Always late.

13
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:35,966
I'm sorry, Mr. Aziz.
There was a disturbance.

14
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,427
Another disturbance.
Always a disturbance with you.

15
00:03:38,594 --> 00:03:41,388
Come on, 21 minutes ago,
in comes order.

16
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:45,851
Harmattan, Burton &amp; Smith.
Eight extra-large deep-dish pizzas.

17
00:03:47,144 --> 00:03:49,146
I told you,
I don't understand that language.

18
00:03:49,313 --> 00:03:51,231
-Speak English.
-You can't make pizza.

19
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:53,275
I can't?
I've been making pizza five years.

20
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:56,236
In eight minutes, I am defaulting on
Joe's 29-minute guarantee.

21
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:59,323
Then, not only am I receiving
no money for these pizzas...

22
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:02,159
...but I will lose the customer forever
to Pizza Yurt.

23
00:04:02,326 --> 00:04:05,495
-Why didn't you send Saleem?
-Saleem was deported yesterday.

24
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,664
-Look-- Smiley.
-What about my cheese pizza?

25
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:10,834
Look, you are my only hope, all right?
You have to make it in time.

26
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:15,172
Peter, you're a nice guy.
But you're just not dependable.

27
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:17,382
This is your last chance.

28
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:22,304
You have to go 42 blocks
in 7 1/2 minutes or your ass is fired.

29
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,849
Go!

30
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:49,540
Hey, what, are you stupid?

31
00:05:11,562 --> 00:05:14,731
Whoa! He stole that guy's pizzas!

32
00:05:23,407 --> 00:05:25,033
I'm gonna get it!

33
00:05:40,632 --> 00:05:42,968
Hey, you guys.
No playing in the streets.

34
00:05:43,135 --> 00:05:44,428
Yes, Mr. Spider-Man.

35
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,388
See you.

36
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:48,724
Way to go, Spidey!

37
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,837
Pizza time.

38
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,176
You're late.

39
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,470
I'm not paying for those.

40
00:07:27,656 --> 00:07:29,199
Elevator.

41
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:49,553
Joe's 29-minute guarantee
is a promise, man.

42
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:54,224
I know to you, Parker, a promise
means nothing. But to me, it's serious.

43
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:56,351
It's serious to me too, Mr. Aziz.

44
00:07:56,518 --> 00:07:59,021
-You're fired. Go.
-Please, I need this job.

45
00:07:59,188 --> 00:08:01,732
-You're fired.
-Look, give me another chance.

46
00:08:10,908 --> 00:08:12,242
You're fired.

47
00:08:12,576 --> 00:08:14,578
-Parker, hello. You're fired.
-Why?

48
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:16,246
Dogs catching Frisbees?

49
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,749
Pigeons in the park?
A couple geezers playing chess?

50
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:20,125
-Boss.
-Not now.

51
00:08:20,292 --> 00:08:23,045
The Buglecould show another side
of New York for a change.

52
00:08:23,212 --> 00:08:26,131
We got six minutes to deadline, Jonah.
We need page one.

53
00:08:26,298 --> 00:08:29,718
I don't pay you to be a sensitive artiste.
I pay you-- Still not now!

54
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:32,471
I pay you because that psycho
Spider-Man will pose for you.

55
00:08:32,638 --> 00:08:34,389
He won't let me take
any more pictures.

56
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:36,140
You turned the whole city
against him.

57
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:37,808
A fact I'm very proud of.

58
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:41,772
Get your pretty little portfolio off my
desk before I go into a diabetic coma.

59
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,275
-It's your wife, she lost her checkbook.
-Thanks for the good news.

60
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:48,779
Please, isn't there any of these shots
you can use? I need the money.

61
00:08:50,155 --> 00:08:51,990
Miss Brant. Get me a violin.

62
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:53,867
Five minutes to deadline, Jonah.

63
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:56,745
Run a picture of a rancid chicken.
Here's the headline:

64
00:08:56,912 --> 00:08:58,789
"Food Poisoning Scare Sweeps City."

65
00:08:58,956 --> 00:09:01,291
-Some food got poisoned?
-I'm a little nauseous.

66
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,293
All right, Mr. Jameson.

67
00:09:05,003 --> 00:09:07,172
It stinks.
Robbie, there's your page one.

68
00:09:07,339 --> 00:09:08,966
"Masked Menace Terrorizes Town."

69
00:09:09,132 --> 00:09:10,717
I told you, he's not a menace.

70
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,469
-I told you--
-I'll take care of it.

71
00:09:12,636 --> 00:09:14,304
-I'll give you 150.
-Three hundred.

72
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,973
That's outrageous.

73
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:18,100
Done. Give this to the girl.

74
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,476
Thank you. Bye-bye.

75
00:09:19,935 --> 00:09:21,436
Hi.

76
00:09:21,645 --> 00:09:23,105
Hey, Pete.

77
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:29,903
I don't think this covers the advance
I gave you a couple weeks ago.

78
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:32,197
-Right.
-Sorry.

79
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:34,658
Hey.

80
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:36,702
Chin up, okay?

81
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,300
Watch it, jerk!

82
00:10:02,019 --> 00:10:03,937
Dr. Connors. Sorry.

83
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:05,647
Where were you headed, Parker?

84
00:10:05,856 --> 00:10:07,107
To your class.

85
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:09,109
My class is over.

86
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:11,486
See me standing here?

87
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:15,449
I'm sorry. I'm trying.
I wanna be here.

88
00:10:15,616 --> 00:10:16,950
Then be here.

89
00:10:18,327 --> 00:10:19,786
Look at you, Peter.

90
00:10:20,329 --> 00:10:24,666
Your grades have been steadily
declining. You're late for class.

91
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,711
You always appear exhausted.

92
00:10:29,171 --> 00:10:31,215
Your paper on fusion is still overdue.

93
00:10:31,381 --> 00:10:34,551
I know. I'm planning to write it
on Dr. Otto Octavius.

94
00:10:34,718 --> 00:10:37,888
Planning is not a major
at this university.

95
00:10:41,225 --> 00:10:43,227
Octavius is a friend of mine.

96
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,562
Better do your research, Parker.

97
00:10:45,896 --> 00:10:49,066
Get it done, or I'm failing you.

98
00:11:10,420 --> 00:11:12,589
Surprise!

99
00:11:12,756 --> 00:11:14,675
Well, say something.

100
00:11:14,842 --> 00:11:16,093
What's the occasion?

101
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:18,846
Really, Peter. It's your birthday!

102
00:11:19,388 --> 00:11:22,182
Whether you want
to remember it or not.

103
00:11:22,558 --> 00:11:25,853
He lives in another reality.
Don't you, Pete?

104
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:27,938
-Hi, M.J.
-Hi.

105
00:11:28,438 --> 00:11:29,815
-Hey, buddy.
-Hey.

106
00:11:29,982 --> 00:11:31,233
Long time, no see.

107
00:11:32,109 --> 00:11:35,279
So how's the play?
I read a great review.

108
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:37,114
It's going fine. It's going good.

109
00:11:37,281 --> 00:11:38,574
She's brilliant in it.

110
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:40,409
Harry sent me roses.

111
00:11:40,576 --> 00:11:43,120
So where you been, pal?
You don't return my calls.

112
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:46,456
I've been busy.

113
00:11:46,623 --> 00:11:50,210
Taking pictures of Spider-Man?
How's the bug these days?

114
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:52,337
The less you see of that man,
the better.

115
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:55,966
Now, let's all go into the other room
and have something to eat.

116
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,426
I'll get the hors d'oeuvres.

117
00:11:57,593 --> 00:11:59,720
So how are things going at Oscorp?

118
00:11:59,887 --> 00:12:02,764
They're great.
I'm head of Special Projects.

119
00:12:02,931 --> 00:12:05,142
We're about to make
a breakthrough on fusion.

120
00:12:05,309 --> 00:12:09,438
How lovely, Harry. Your father
would be so proud, rest his soul.

121
00:12:09,605 --> 00:12:10,898
Thank you.

122
00:12:11,315 --> 00:12:15,068
We're actually funding
one of your idols, Pete. Otto Octavius.

123
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:17,654
-I'm writing a paper on him.
-You want to meet him?

124
00:12:17,821 --> 00:12:19,114
You'd introduce me?

125
00:12:19,281 --> 00:12:22,492
You bet. Octavius is
gonna put Oscorp on the map...

126
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,661
...in a way my father
never even dreamed of.

127
00:12:24,828 --> 00:12:26,788
M.J., could you give me a hand?

128
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:30,751
She's waiting for you, pal.

129
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:32,669
What do you mean?

130
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:35,339
The way she looks at you
or doesn't look at you.

131
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:37,216
However you want to look at it.

132
00:12:37,591 --> 00:12:39,760
I don't have time for girls right now.

133
00:12:39,927 --> 00:12:41,261
Why, are you dead?

134
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:43,013
I've been kind of busy.

135
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:44,806
Taking pictures of your friend?

136
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:47,809
Could we get off that subject?

137
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:51,313
I want us to be friends, Harry.
I want us to trust each other.

138
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,148
Then be honest with me.

139
00:12:53,565 --> 00:12:56,276
If you knew who he was,
would you tell me?

140
00:13:01,073 --> 00:13:03,450
Peter, don't you understand
how I feel?

141
00:13:03,617 --> 00:13:05,536
I want this guy dead.

142
00:13:05,702 --> 00:13:08,539
The same way you want the guy
who killed your Uncle Ben dead.

143
00:13:16,046 --> 00:13:19,508
I'm sorry. I don't mean to
rag on you on your birthday.

144
00:13:21,677 --> 00:13:23,720
You're my buddy, you know that.

145
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:27,015
You're family, Pete.

146
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:31,270
My father loved you.
You were like a son to him.

147
00:13:37,109 --> 00:13:39,069
Thank you, Harry.

148
00:14:12,895 --> 00:14:14,396
May.

149
00:14:14,563 --> 00:14:16,106
Oh, what, Ben?

150
00:14:17,441 --> 00:14:19,401
Wait.

151
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:21,028
-Aunt May.
-Oh, my.

152
00:14:21,445 --> 00:14:26,658
Oh, Peter. Oh, for a second there,
I thought I was years ago.

153
00:14:28,869 --> 00:14:30,787
Everybody's gone, aren't they?

154
00:14:31,246 --> 00:14:32,915
Did they have a good time?

155
00:14:33,415 --> 00:14:34,666
I'm sure they did.

156
00:14:36,502 --> 00:14:40,339
-You okay?
-Of course. But you go home.

157
00:14:40,964 --> 00:14:46,136
And be careful. I don't like that
scooter thing you drive around.

158
00:14:46,887 --> 00:14:48,096
I'm worried about you.

159
00:14:48,514 --> 00:14:53,477
You're so alone.
And I saw the letter from the bank.

160
00:14:53,644 --> 00:14:56,104
Oh, my. You did?

161
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:57,940
Oh, well.

162
00:14:58,106 --> 00:14:59,525
So?

163
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,777
I'm a little behind.

164
00:15:02,778 --> 00:15:04,488
Everybody is.

165
00:15:05,155 --> 00:15:08,158
Anyway, I don't want
to talk about it anymore.

166
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:12,037
I'm tired,
and you better start back home.

167
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:16,333
Here, kiddo. Happy birthday.

168
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,335
You need it more than I do.

169
00:15:18,502 --> 00:15:21,004
-No, I can't take that from you.
-Yes, you can!

170
00:15:21,171 --> 00:15:23,215
You can take this money from me.

171
00:15:23,382 --> 00:15:26,134
For God's sake, it's not much.
Now, take it!

172
00:15:26,301 --> 00:15:28,804
And don't you dare leave it here.

173
00:15:28,971 --> 00:15:30,889
Oh, I'm sorry.

174
00:15:32,099 --> 00:15:35,644
It's just that I miss
your uncle Ben so much.

175
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:42,693
Can you believe that it's two years
next month since he was taken?

176
00:15:45,028 --> 00:15:47,239
I think to myself at times...

177
00:15:48,407 --> 00:15:52,703
...were I to face the one responsible
for what happened, I'd....

178
00:15:53,745 --> 00:15:55,789
Oh, I don't know what I'd do.

179
00:16:02,337 --> 00:16:03,922
Now...

180
00:16:05,841 --> 00:16:08,552
...you better take
the rest of your cake home.

181
00:16:23,317 --> 00:16:24,818
Hey.

182
00:16:24,985 --> 00:16:27,070
Hey. You're still here.

183
00:16:28,238 --> 00:16:29,823
I saw your billboard on Bleecker.

184
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:33,368
Isn't it funny?
I'm really kind of embarrassed.

185
00:16:33,535 --> 00:16:37,497
Don't be. It's nice.
I get to see you every day now.

186
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,082
The photographer liked my face.

187
00:16:39,249 --> 00:16:42,085
I was only supposed to be
in the catalogue.

188
00:16:42,252 --> 00:16:45,756
Then I got the part in the play.
Everything at once.

189
00:16:45,923 --> 00:16:47,925
Your dream came true.

190
00:16:48,592 --> 00:16:50,260
How about yours?

191
00:16:52,387 --> 00:16:55,390
I'm fine.

192
00:16:57,434 --> 00:16:59,811
I wish you'd come see the play.

193
00:16:59,978 --> 00:17:02,189
You're the one who
always encouraged me.

194
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:04,942
I plan to.

195
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:12,281
I liked seeing you tonight, Peter.

196
00:17:14,535 --> 00:17:16,286
Oh, boy, yeah.

197
00:17:16,954 --> 00:17:19,873
"Oh, boy, yeah" what?

198
00:17:24,377 --> 00:17:26,046
Nothing.

199
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,261
Do you want to say something?

200
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:39,852
I...

201
00:17:45,816 --> 00:17:47,067
...was...

202
00:17:48,068 --> 00:17:51,321
...wondering if you're still
in the Village.

203
00:18:00,497 --> 00:18:02,499
You're such a mystery.

204
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:14,553
Peter.

205
00:18:15,971 --> 00:18:17,514
What?

206
00:18:22,477 --> 00:18:24,188
Happy birthday.

207
00:18:32,863 --> 00:18:35,032
I'm seeing somebody now.

208
00:18:37,075 --> 00:18:39,161
-Therapy.
-No.

209
00:18:39,453 --> 00:18:41,121
A person, a man.

210
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:43,665
You mean, like a boyfriend?

211
00:18:43,832 --> 00:18:46,502
Well, like I like him.

212
00:18:49,713 --> 00:18:51,048
What?

213
00:18:51,882 --> 00:18:53,425
Nothing.

214
00:18:54,301 --> 00:18:57,554
That's good, you know?
Companionship....

215
00:18:59,223 --> 00:19:00,891
May be more than that.

216
00:19:02,017 --> 00:19:03,560
More?

217
00:19:04,311 --> 00:19:05,729
I don't know.

218
00:19:07,064 --> 00:19:09,316
I'm coming to see your play
tomorrow night.

219
00:19:12,361 --> 00:19:15,322
-You're coming?
-I'll be there.

220
00:19:16,281 --> 00:19:17,991
Don't disappoint me.

221
00:19:19,409 --> 00:19:21,078
I won't.

222
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,844
Rent.

223
00:19:40,681 --> 00:19:43,350
-Hi.
-Hi. What's "hi"?

224
00:19:43,517 --> 00:19:45,060
Can I spend it?

225
00:19:45,769 --> 00:19:47,688
I have a paycheck due this week
and--

226
00:19:47,855 --> 00:19:51,191
-You're a month late again. Again.
-I promise as soon as--

227
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:54,862
If promises were crackers,
my daughter would be fat.

228
00:19:55,445 --> 00:19:59,950
I'm really sorry, Mr. Ditkovitch. All I got
is this 20 for the rest of the week.

229
00:20:00,617 --> 00:20:02,202
"Sorry" doesn't pay the rent.

230
00:20:02,369 --> 00:20:07,207
And don't try to sneak past me. I have
ears like a cat and eyes like a rodent.

231
00:20:08,917 --> 00:20:11,795
-Thanks, Mr. Ditkovitch.
-Hi, Pete.

232
00:21:05,641 --> 00:21:07,226
Hello?

233
00:21:14,608 --> 00:21:16,318
Rent?

234
00:21:21,406 --> 00:21:23,784
Doctor? Mr. Osborn's here.

235
00:21:23,951 --> 00:21:27,955
Nobel Prize, Otto. Nobel Prize.
And we'll all be rich.

236
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:29,748
It's not about the prizes, Harry.

237
00:21:29,915 --> 00:21:31,708
But you need money.
You need Oscorp.

238
00:21:31,875 --> 00:21:33,126
Who do we have here?

239
00:21:33,293 --> 00:21:35,045
This is my good friend
I called you about.

240
00:21:35,212 --> 00:21:36,880
He got me through
high-school science.

241
00:21:37,047 --> 00:21:40,092
Peter Parker, sir.
I'm writing a paper on you for--

242
00:21:40,259 --> 00:21:41,718
I know what you're doing here...

243
00:21:41,885 --> 00:21:44,054
...but I don't have time
to talk to students now.

244
00:21:45,055 --> 00:21:46,890
But Oscorp pays the bills, so....

245
00:21:47,057 --> 00:21:49,393
That's why I have to take off.
Board meeting.

246
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:52,896
But my job is done here.
Got you two geniuses together.

247
00:21:53,063 --> 00:21:57,693
Good luck tomorrow, Otto.
Nobel Prize. We'll see you in Sweden!

248
00:22:00,404 --> 00:22:01,905
Interesting fellow, your friend.

249
00:22:02,531 --> 00:22:04,241
I won't take much of your time.

250
00:22:04,408 --> 00:22:08,745
Now I remember you. You're Connors'
student. He tells me you're brilliant.

251
00:22:09,538 --> 00:22:11,623
He also tells me you're lazy.

252
